        {
            "id": "index_first_occurrence",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "If a value appears multiple times, `index()` only returns the position of the **first occurrence**."
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "numbers = [5, 10, 5, 20, 5]\nposition = numbers.index(5)\nprint(position)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "0"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "Even though `5` appears three times, `index()` returns `0` (the first occurrence)."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "quick_check_first_occurrence",
